meanings.definition: スコグボライト（仮称）※専門用語/造語の可能性
meanings.english_definition: A term that appears to be a specialized technical word or possible neologism with unclear definition. May relate to geology/mineralogy given the '-lite' suffix.

etymology.value: Uncertain. Likely derived from Swedish 'skog' (forest) + Greek-derived suffix '-lite' (stone/mineral), suggesting a possible Scandinavian-origin mineral name. May be a misspelling or specialized term.

usage_notes.explanation: This term does not appear in standard English dictionaries and may be: 1) A highly specialized technical term 2) A misspelling (possibly of 'scorodite' or similar mineral names) 3) A constructed word from Scandinavian languages 4) A proper noun. Verification in technical literature is recommended.
